    • closure

      public static final BeanTypeList closure(TypeMirror t, Predicate<? super TypeMirror> typeFilter, Visitors visitors)
      Returns a non-null BeanTypeList containing the set of types t bears.
      Parameters:
      t - the TypeMirror whose type closure will be returned as a BeanTypeList; must not be null; must be either a declared type, an intersection type or a type variable
      typeFilter - a Predicate used to test a given TypeMirror; if its test(Object) method returns true for a given TypeMirror, the TypeMirror will be included in the returned BeanTypeList; may be null
      visitors - a Visitors providing access to a type closure visitor; must not be null
      Returns:
      a non-null BeanTypeList
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if t or visitors is null
      IllegalArgumentException - if t is neither a declared type, an intersection type nor a type variable
      See Also:
      • Visitors.typeClosureVisitor()

    • legalBeanType

      public static final boolean legalBeanType(TypeMirror t)
      Returns true if and only if t is non-null and a legal bean type.
      Parameters:
      t - the TypeMirror in question; must not be null
      Returns:
      true if and only if t is non-null and a legal bean type; false otherwise
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if t is null
